#sw-tagline
  %p Many teams use chef to manage their production machines, but developers often build their development boxes by hand.  SoloWizard makes it painless to create a customized chef solo script to get your development machine humming: mysql, sublime text, .bash_profile tweaks to OS-X settings - it's all there!

#sw-explained
  #sw-description
    %p.built-upon
      SoloWizard is built ontop of 3 popular and well supported open source projects:
      = "#{link_to 'Chef Solo', 'http://wiki.opscode.com/display/chef/Chef+Solo', :target => '_blank'}, the #{link_to 'pivotal_workstation', 'https://github.com/pivotal/pivotal_workstation', :target => '_blank'} cookbook, and the #{link_to 'soloist', 'https://github.com/mkocher/soloist', :target => '_blank'} gem.".html_safe

    .dependencies
      %p Dependencies:
      %ul
        %li OS-X Mountain Lion
        %li
          X-Code installed
          =link_to "(install how-to)", "#"


